HB 326 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Muscarello
Abstract: Requires that the police chief of the village of Tickaw reside within the corporate
limits of the village.
Present law requires that an elected police chief of a municipality, except a village, be an
elector of the municipality. Further requires that a candidate for police chief be domiciled
for at least the immediately preceding year in the municipality.
Present law requires an elected police chief of a village to reside within the boundaries of
the parish in which the village is located.
Proposed law makes an exception for the village of Tickfaw. Requires that the elected
police chief reside within the corporate limits of the village and requires a candidate for
police chief to have been domiciled in the village for the year preceding qualifying.
(Adds R.S. 33:385.1(B)(3))
